          <h2 class="welcome-head">Welcome!</h2>    
          <div class="welcome-left-h3">About Us</div>
          <p class="middle-par">
              Recyclopse is a recycling company that helps make recycling beneficial for everybody!
              We take in recyclable materials from companies, sort the recycling, 
              sell the recycled materials, and transport any excess waste.
              <br />
          </p>
          <div class="welcome-left-h3">What can I recycle?</div>
          <p class="middle-par">
              The three categories of recyclables are 
              <b>Bottles and Cans, Paper, and Cardboard</b>. 
              Anything that doesnâ€™t belong in these bins should be placed in 
              the trash instead. See the detailed list below:
              <br />
          </p>
          <p class="welcome-left">
              <u>Bottles and Cans:</u>
              <ul class = "welcome-left-ul">
                  <li>Glass bottles and jars</li>
                  <li>Aluminum and Tin Cans</li>
                  <li>Plastic bottles (containers with narrow neck) and jugs (bottles with a handle)</li>
              </ul>
          </p>
          <p class="welcome-left-2">
            <b>Note:</b>
              Bottles and Cans should be emptied, washed, and dried. Caps should 
              be removed whenever possible. They must have contained food or beverages. 
              Glass containers from labs are not accepted. <br/>
              <br/>
        </p>
          <p class="welcome-left">
              <u>Paper:</u>
              <ul class="welcome-left-ul">
                  <li>Office paper, newspapers, junk mail and greeting cards, magazines</li>
                  <li>Paperback books, phone books, and notebooks (metal binding is accepted!)</li>
                  <li>Paper bags and packing paper</li>
                  <li>Paperboard (heavier, non-corrugated paper)</li>
              </ul>
          </p>
          <p class="welcome-left-2">
              <b>Not acceptable Paper products:</b>
              <ul class="welcome-left-ul-2">
              <li>Hardback books</li>
              <li>Cartons and aseptic containers</li>
              <li>Butcher paper</li>
              <li>Egg cartons</li>
              <li>Paper cups and plates</li>
              <li>Napkins and paper towels</li>
              <li>Note: Paper should be greater than 2x2 inches in size, otherwise it should be 
                   thrown away or composted if it is 100% paper. </li>
              </ul>
          </p>
          <p class="welcome-left">
              <u>Cardboard:</u>
              <p class="welcome-left-cb">
                  Only <b>Flattened, corrugated</b> cardboard is accepted. Contents must be emptied 
                  and the cardboard must not be contaminated with food and oil. Must be placed 
                  in a marked container <b>outside</b> your building, located near the dumpsters.
  
  
              </p>
          </p>
